  "text": "Proof. Since R is a cordfree circuit and hRi is infinite it follows that hRi is a cocompact reflection group of the hyperbolic plane H 2 or the Euclidean plane E 2 , see for example [CITATION_1] . In particular hRi acts e¤ectively, properly and cocompactly on a contractible manifold. The main result of [CITATION_2] then implies that the Coxeter system ðhRi; RÞ is strongly reflection-rigid. Thus MðRÞ is strongly reflection-rigid and R is geometric by Proposition 5.2. r",
